      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIGLETTA (9) has a fitness edge over the bulk of these third-up and can overcome the awkward gate. Tongue-tie goes on today and the extra trip is in her favour after finishing a close-up third over 1000m at Wyong. Expected to go close. GAMP (6) unlucky not to shed her Maiden tag last prep and looks primed for this with the two solid trials. Ran second to Bev's Nine last July, and no excuses in this winnable contest. UBER IN (7) handy mare who returns for her second campaign. Given plenty of time to develop further and the two recent trials suggest she's back in good order. Value prospect. VERY SIRIUS (10) Zoustar filly from California Salto on debut for the David Pfieffer stable. Two recent trials had merit and drawn to map well. Sure to be thereabouts.",
